        "body": "@jsignell I hacked my own solution together:\r\n```python\r\nchunk_sizes, = dask.compute([b.sum() for b in mask.flatten().blocks])\r\n\r\nlocs = np.argwhere(mask)\r\nlocs._chunks = (\r\n\ttuple(chunk_sizes),\r\n\ttuple([1] * locs.shape[-1])\r\n)\r\n```\r\nNot sure whether I made a mistake but in my use cases this worked great.\r\n\r\n--------\r\nAnyways, if I would compute `locs` in memory we would have an array of size:\r\n```\r\n75781858 * sizeof(int64) * 3 dimensions = \r\n= 75781858 * 8 * 3 \r\n= ~1734MB`\r\n```\r\nHowever, a single call to `np.empty()` allocates 3614MB. Why?",
